   citrandarin rootstock x639 {[}Cleopatra mandarin (C. reticulata Blanco)
   x trifoliate orange (Poncirus trifoliata L.)] were significantly more
   productive than trees on any other rootstock tested for `Oroblanco' and
   all rootstocks except Swingle citrumelo (C. paradisi x P. trifoliata)
   and Cleopatra mandarin for `Melogold'. Cumulative production of
   `Oroblanco' on x639, through year 9, was 50\% higher than for Swingle or
   Volkamer lemon {[}C. Union (L.)], which were the next highest in yield.
