   fewer than 50 fruit total in the 9 years of this study. Carrizo citrange
   (C. sinensis Osbeck x P. trifoliata) produced the smallest trees with
   both scion varieties, reflecting poor adaptation of this rootstock to
   the calcareous soil at the trial site. As expected, acidity of
   `Oroblanco' and `Melogold' was much lower than would be observed for
   grapefruit when fall harvested, with similar total soluble solids (TSS),
