   practices and for assuring optimal quality of grapes. Our study examined
   responses of four new rootstocks selected for resistance to water and
   salt stresses, iron chlorosis, vigor reduction, and enhanced potassium
   (K) and magnesium (Mg) uptake efficiency. The new rootstocks are the
   result of crossing various species of Vitis (riparia, cordifolia,
